Fashion MNIST - Sample Project¶

The following is a (very simple) example of a README file that allows the user to re-run data pre-processing, training, validation and evaluation. Note that you will likely perform more extensive hyperparameter tuning and train more models. You should inform the user how this hyperparameter was performed and ideally provide code for them to reproduce this process.

Download data (and move into project folder): https://www.kaggle.com/zalando-research/fashionmnist

Install requirements¶

In [ ]:
! pip install -r requirements.txt

Training & validation¶

  • In order to write data before running training please set --write_data option to True (False by default).
  • During training, the validation accuracy will be evaluated in order to choose the optimal number of epochs to train models.
  • A log file will be generated during training to record validation loss and accuracy for future reference.

Directory Structure¶

sample_project
-checkpoints
   |
    ----> cnn
          |
           ---> checkpoint_CNN_epoch_1
                       .
                       . 
                       .
           ---> checkpoint_CNN_epoch_100
    ----> mlp
          |
           ---> checkpoint_MLP_epoch_1
                       .
                       . 
                       .
           ---> checkpoint_MLP_epoch_100
- fashiomnist
    |
     ---> fashion-mnist_test.csv
     ---> fashion-mnist_train.csv
     ---> test.csv
     ---> train.csv
     ---> val.csv
        |
        ===> fashion-mnist_test.csv
        ===> fashion-mnist_train.csv
        ===> test.csv
        ===> train.csv
        ===> val.csv
- figs
    |
     ---> CNN_training_vis.png
     ---> MLP_training_vis.png   
- logs
    |
     ---> cnn
        |
         ===> eval_logs
             |
              ---> CNN_5.json
         ===> CNN_130320_193314.json 
     ---> mlp
        |
         ===> eval_logs
             |
              ---> MLP_5.json
         ===> MLP_130320_184810.json

- models
    |
    ----> __init__.py
    ----> cnn.py
    ----> mlp.py
- utils
    ---> Datasets.py
    ---> params.py
    ---> plotting.py
eval.py
hparams.yaml
main.py

requirements.txt

import json

import pandas as pd

    mlp_log = json.load(f)

with open("logs/cnn/eval_logs/CNN_5.json") as f:
    cnn_log = json.load(f)

                    "accuracy":["{0:.2f}\u00B1 {1:.4f}".format(mlp_log["mean_acc"], np.sqrt(mlp_log["var_acc"])),
                                "{0:.2f}\u00B1 {1:.4f}".format(cnn_log["mean_acc"], np.sqrt(cnn_log["var_acc"]))]})
